<h2>Specific climate indicators for April 2020</h2>
<br><br>
The high temperatures in Central Europe caused a decrease in the number of frost days in the Alps. Although still higher than in the surrounding regions, the number of frost days in the Alps was much lower than normal (Figure 3).
<br><br>
<a href="../images/apr2020/Stateofclimate_IndicesTest_fd_2020_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_fdETCCDI_baselayers_overlay_2020-04-15T12-00-00Z_large.png" target="_blank"><img alt="" src="../images/apr2020/Stateofclimate_IndicesTest_fd_2020_month_nc_baselayers_world_polygons_fdETCCDI_baselayers_overlay_2020-04-15T12-00-00Z.png" ></a>
