<h2>The weather in April 2020</h2>
<h3>Temperature deviations and extremes</h3>
<br><br>
<br><br>
In Europe, temperatures were well above average in a number of western countries, but below average in the northeast.
MeteoSwiss reported an average April temperature for Switzerland that was 3&deg;C warmer than the 1991-2020 average and almost 5&deg;C warmer than the average for 1871-1900. Only April 2007 was substantially warmer. M&#233;t&#233;o-France reported the country's third warmest April in a record extending back to 1900.
Temperatures elsewhere over Europe were less extreme. Colder than average conditions over the east of the continent were in marked contrast to the much above average temperatures experienced there in the late-autumn and winter months of 2019/20.
<br><br>
<br><br>
